From 376ae1ee7c69e4ff68a6c3f9931d8f80e7fa01a3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Balamurugan Ramar <quic_bramar@quicinc.com>
Date: Thu, 10 Apr 2025 23:25:42 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] mac80211: hw settings for EHT

Add details in ieee80211_register_hw() for EHT support (yes/no),
and include EHT capabilities maximum length for scan buffer length
calculation.

Signed-off-by: Aloka Dixit <quic_alokad@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Balamurugan Ramar <quic_bramar@quicinc.com>
---
 net/mac80211/main.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/net/mac80211/main.c b/net/mac80211/main.c
index bc8cd75..302c9b2 100644
--- a/net/mac80211/main.c
+++ b/net/mac80211/main.c
@@ -1346,9 +1346,9 @@ int ieee80211_register_hw(struct ieee80211_hw *hw)
 				return -EINVAL;
 		}
 
-		/* HT, VHT, HE require QoS, thus >= 4 queues */
+		/* HT, VHT, HE, EHT require QoS, thus >= 4 queues */
 		if (WARN_ON(local->hw.queues < IEEE80211_NUM_ACS &&
-			    (supp_ht || supp_vht || supp_he)))
+			    (supp_ht || supp_vht || supp_he || supp_eht)))
 			return -EINVAL;
 
 		/* EHT requires HE support */
-- 
2.34.1

